            <h2>Official rules</h2>
            <div class="separator"></div>

            <p class="mt-3">
                NO PURCHASE NECESSARY TO ENTER OR WIN. A PURCHASE OF ANY KIND WILL NOT INCREASE YOUR CHANCES OF WINNING.  VOID WHERE PROHIBITED OR RESTRICTED BY LAW. OPEN ONLY TO LEGAL U.S. RESIDENTS 18 YEARS OLD OR OLDER.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                The Juno 2019 Scholarship (“Sweepstakes”) is sponsored by LeverEdge Association. (“Sponsor”).
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                1. NO PURCHASE NECESSARY.  All federal, state and local laws and regulations apply.  Void where prohibited or restricted by law.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                2. Eligibility: Sweepstakes open to natural persons who are legal residents of the U.S., at least 18 years old at time of entry; who are currently enrolled in a graduate degree program or will be enrolled in an graduate degree program in Fall 2019 or have completed a graduate degree program. Employees of Sponsor and their immediate family members (including mother, father, sister, brother, daughter, son or spouse), regardless of where they live; or persons who reside in the same household, whether related or not, are not eligible.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                3. Entry Period: The Sweepstakes begins on April 5th, 2019 at 9:00AM EST and ends September 30th, 2019 at 11:59PM EST (“Entry Period”). All times determined by Sponsor’s clock (ET).
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                4. How to Enter: Persons who meet the eligibility requirements may complete the survey, and submit the completed survey for entry into the Sweepstakes. Limit one (1) entry per person. Entries made by commercial sweepstakes subscription notification and/or entering services are ineligible. Entrants are responsible for any charges of online service providers or wireless carriers. Each entrant may enter using only one (1) account. In the event of a dispute as to the identity of an entrant, entrant will be deemed the authorized account holder at time of entry. Should more than one (1) entry per person be received, Sponsor reserves the right to void all such entries. Sponsor is not responsible for late, lost, misdirected or scrambled entries. Incomplete entries will not be accepted. All entries become property of Sponsor and will not be acknowledged or returned. By submitting an entry, each entrant represents and warrants that he/she has read and accepted these Official Rules and agrees that Sponsor’s decisions are final and binding in all matters relating to this Sweepstakes.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                5. Selection of Winner: The Sponsor will count the number of eligible entrants from each program and calculate the penetration at each program. The program with the highest penetration will be selected as the winning program. Penetration is defined as the sum total of eligible entrants from said program divided by the total active enrollment of that program. A random drawing will be held on or about Oct 1st, 2019 from all eligible entries from entrants in the winning program, received during the Entry Period. Odds of winning depend on the number of eligible entries from each program, the number of eligible entries from the entrant’s program and the total number of eligible entries.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                6. Prize: One (1) $5,000 payment to the winner. Prize will be awarded, “AS IS”, “AS AVAILABLE”, without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including without limitation any implied warranty of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose. All federal, state and local taxes and duties are the winner’s responsibility.  Prize may not be transferred, substituted or redeemed for cash.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                7. Notification of Winner: Potential winner will be notified by email and must respond within seven (7) days or prize may be forfeited and an alternate potential winner selected. Potential winner is subject to Sponsor’s verification of eligibility and compliance with law. In the event a potential winner is deemed ineligible or unable to accept a prize for any reason, a new potential winner will be selected following the procedures outlined above.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                8. Prize Delivery:  Prize will be disbursed to the recipient via check.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-3">
                9. Privacy: All personal information collected in connection with the Sweepstakes is subject to Sponsor’s privacy policy at https://joinjuno.com/privacy. Entrants agree to be contacted by Sponsor regarding the Sweepstakes and to receive advertising and promotional communications from Sponsor unless and until they opt out, such as provided on the emails or in Sponsor’s privacy policy.  By entering, each entrant agrees, where lawful, that Sponsor Entities may use entrant's survey response, entry, name, city of residence, likeness, voice, biographical information, statements or actions for publication, advertising and promotional purposes without any opportunity for inspection or approval, and without further consideration.
